<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-15T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-15T13:00:00-05:00" n="855" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d855">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111 A.R.–Subs/4: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-15T13:00:00-05:00">June 15,
                                    1940—1 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 8:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>107. In response Department’s circular of June 13, 8 p.m., Foreign
                                Minister<note n="19a" xml:id="d855fn19a">Julio Tobar Donoso.</note>
                            says Ecuador has complied with all recommendations Inter-American
                            Neutrality Committee: Ecuadoran decree No. 12<note n="20" xml:id="d855fn20">Decree No. 12 of March 27, 1940, Pan American
                                Union, Law and Treaty Series No. 14, p. 12.</note>
                            <pb facs="0793" n="781" xml:id="pg_781"/> covers submarines, 15<note n="21" xml:id="d855fn21">Decree No. 15 of March 31, 1940, Pan
                                American Union, Law and Treaty Series No. 14, p. 14.</note>
                            internment and No. 19<note n="22" xml:id="d855fn22">Decree No. 19 of
                                April 30, 1940, <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 18.</note> merchant
                            ships and auxiliary vessels.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>